{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fixedSize","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size.","type":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ideal size"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of its children both dimensions:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may not be the effect you want."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can think of "},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the creation of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"counter proposal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view, and the specific effects of "},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" depends on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"particular view and how you have configured it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertical dimensions, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/document